# Payments Domain

## Glossary

| Term | Definition |
|------|-----------|
| **connector** | A payment processor integration (e.g., Stripe connector, Adyen connector) |
| **processor / PSP** | Payment Service Provider — the underlying payment company (Stripe, Adyen, Braintree, Checkout.com, etc.) |
| **MIT** | Merchant-Initiated Transaction — charge triggered by the merchant without customer present |
| **CIT** | Customer-Initiated Transaction — charge triggered by a customer action in real time |
| **3DS / 3D Secure** | Authentication protocol adding a second layer of identity verification for card payments |
| **FRM** | Fraud & Risk Management — rules and models to detect and block fraudulent transactions |
| **payout** | Disbursement flow — sending money to a recipient (vendor, contractor, user) |
| **recon** | Reconciliation — matching payment records across systems to detect discrepancies |
| **routing rule** | Logic that selects which connector to use for a given payment (volume-based, rule-based) |
| **surcharge** | Extra fee added on top of a payment amount |
| **dispute** | A chargeback challenge initiated by a merchant contesting a reversal |
| **chargeback** | Forced reversal of a payment, initiated by the cardholder through their bank |
| **acquirer** | Bank that processes card payments on behalf of the merchant |
| **issuer** | Bank that issued the customer's payment card |
| **BIN / IIN** | Bank Identification Number / Issuer Identification Number — first 6–8 digits of a card number |
| **tokenization** | Replacing sensitive card data with a non-sensitive token for storage/reuse |
| **PCI-DSS** | Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard — compliance requirements for handling card data |
| **webhook** | HTTP callback from the payment processor to notify of payment events asynchronously |
| **idempotency key** | Unique key sent with an API request to ensure it is not processed more than once |
| **payment intent** | A record representing the customer's intent to pay; tracks the payment lifecycle |
| **payment attempt** | A single try to complete a payment intent (may retry on failure) |
| **mandate** | Authorization to charge a customer repeatedly (subscriptions, recurring payments) |
| **EMI** | Equated Monthly Instalment — splitting a payment into fixed monthly amounts |
| **UPI** | Unified Payments Interface — Indian real-time payment system |
| **NEFT / IMPS / RTGS** | Indian bank transfer methods (National Electronic Funds Transfer, Immediate Payment Service, Real-Time Gross Settlement) |

